The paper deals with the optimization of convolutional neural networks for image recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of separable filters, which is a technique for reducing computational complexity, and this is a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed method on CPU or GPU, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
